<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge,chrome=1">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Emojinator</title>
    <meta name="description" content="">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
    <%= javascript_include_tag "application" %>
    <!-- boostrap -->
    <!-- Latest compiled and minified CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.1/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <!-- Optional theme -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.1/css/bootstrap-theme.min.css">
    <link rel="icon" href="favicon.ico">
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "application", media: "all" %>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h1><%= image_tag "favicon.png", style: "width: 100px; padding: 15px;" %>Translate This Into Emoji!</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <h4>Thanks for your help! That's all we have for you at this stage, but we'll be in touch in the future with further developments!</h4>
      <h4>Take a look at <%= link_to 'all completed translations', :results %> if you want to see what everyone else did, too.</h4>
      <p>(Safari or other unicode emoji smart browsers only, sorry). Also note, we didn't share this while you were working because we genuinely want to see what everyone comes up with independently, so please don't share this with others.</p>
    </div>

    <script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.1/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
